  "description": "The ocean breathing at the thermocline — where warm surface water meets cold deep water. LFO2 at 0.067 Hz (one breath per 15 seconds) modulates both pitch wobble and pressure compression simultaneously. The sound swells and retreats like a thermal boundary layer oscillating. Filter cutoff at 450 Hz sits at the thermocline of the frequency spectrum — warm above, cold below.",
